    slug: "qurbani-aqeeqah-aur-ashra-zil-hajja",
    description: `Qurbani, Aqeeqah aur Ashra Zil Hajja is an Urdu-language Islamic book that provides a comprehensive guide to three important religious practices: the ritual sacrifice of Eid al-Adha (qurbani), the birth celebration sacrifice (aqeeqah), and the first ten days of the month of Dhul Hijjah (ashra-e-zil-hijjah). These three topics are closely interconnected, as they all relate to the month of Dhul Hijjah — the twelfth and final month of the Islamic calendar — and the rituals associated with it. The book serves as a practical reference for Muslims who want to understand and correctly perform these important acts of worship according to the teachings of the Quran and the authenticated Sunnah.

The section on qurbani (Eid sacrifice) covers the complete rulings related to the annual udhiyah sacrifice performed on the days of Eid al-Adha. Topics include the obligation and virtues of qurbani, the conditions that make it mandatory, the types of animals that can be sacrificed and their minimum age requirements, the procedure for performing the sacrifice, the distribution of the meat, and common mistakes to avoid. The author provides detailed guidance based on the major schools of Islamic jurisprudence, with emphasis on the evidence from the Quran and hadith that underpins each ruling. Practical instructions are given for those who arrange their qurbani through agents or charitable organizations in other countries.

The aqeeqah section covers the Islamic practice of sacrificing an animal upon the birth of a child, including the recommended time of performance, the number of animals to be sacrificed (one goat for a girl, two for a boy, according to the majority view), the conditions for the sacrificial animal, and the recommended practices associated with the aqeeqah gathering. The section on the first ten days of Dhul Hijjah explains why these days are considered the most blessed days of the year, detailing the specific acts of worship recommended during this period — including fasting, increased remembrance of Allah, charity, recitation of the Quran, and repentance. The book presents all material with source references, clear Urdu explanations, and a practical focus that helps readers implement the teachings in their daily lives during the blessed month of Dhul Hijjah.`,
